title: Episode #5.21
description: Johnny Cash sings, "Big River" and "City of New Orleans". George Lindsey performs "Mountain Dew" and Jean Shepard sings, "Come On, Phone" and "Slippin' Away". Other songs performed are "Rocky Top", "Cowboy Convention" and "My Maria".

cast.name: Danny Davis and the Nashville Brass

title: Episode #9.8
description: Loretta Lynn sings "Why Can't He Be You?" and "She's Got You". Ernest Rey performs "Trixie" and Sons of the Pioneers perform "Tumbling Tumbleweeds".

title: Episode #9.9
description: Eddie Rabbitt sings "I'm a Little Bit Lonesome" and "We Can't Go on Living Like This". Roy Clark sings "I Don't Know How to Tell Her". Buck Owens and the Buckaroos perform "I Washed My Hands in Muddy Water".

title: Episode #9.10
description: Songs include "Bright Lights, Big City" and "When the Snow is on the Roses".

title: Episode #9.11
description: Tom T. Hall sings "It's All in the Game" and "Your Man Loves You, Honey". Sons of the Pioneers perform "Cool Water" and The Hagers duet with "Daydreams About Night Things". Roy Clark sings "Kids".

title: Episode dated 3 December 1977
description: Don Williams sings "She Never Knew Me" and "Some Broken Hearts Never Mend". Dave & Sugar do "That's the Way Love Should Be".

title: Episode dated 10 December 1977
description: Floyd Cramer sings "Last Date" and Kenny Roberts sings "She Taught Me to Yodel".

title: Episode dated 17 December 1977
description: Dennis Weaver, Buck Owens and the cast join in with "Make Love to Life". Susan Raye sings "Saturday Night to Sunday Quiet".

title: Episode dated 24 December 1977
description: Johnny Paycheck sings "I Sleep with her Memory Every Night" and Mel Street sings "Country Pride".
